    dc:creator "Marinho, Pedro; Bang, Davi L.; Vidigal, Izadora; Giaretta, Ariovaldo A." ;
    dc:date "2022" ;
    dc:title "A New Cryptic Species of Boana (Hylinae: Cophomantini) of the B. polytaenia Clade from the Brazilian Atlantic Forest" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7818747>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7818749>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7818751>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7818745>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7818753>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7818755>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7818759>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7818757> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7818747>
    dc:description "FIG. 2. Holotype of Boana guarinimirim sp. nov. (CFBH 46043) from Castelo, Parque Estadual do Forno Grande (Espírito Santo, Brazil): (A) dorsal and (B) ventral views (SVL = 24.1 mm), (C) hand and (D) foot." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7818747/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7818749>
    dc:description "FIG. 3. Comparison of (A) Boana guarinimirim sp. nov. with other species in the B. polytaenia clade: (B) B. cipoensis (AAG-UFU 0027), (C) B. buriti (AAG-UFU 0433), and (D) B. stenocephala (AAG-UFU 4827). Arrows in (A) indicate the supracloacal crest and the calcar appendage, absent in B–D. Specimens are not to scale." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7818749/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7818751>
    dc:description "FIG. 4. Advertisement calls (spectrograms and corresponding oscillograms) of (A–B) B. guarinimirim sp. nov. (sound files: Boana_guarinimirimFornoGrandeES2aPM_AAGm671 and Boana_guarinimirimFornoGrandeES3aPM_AAGm671, respectively); (C–D) Boana sp. 4 (sound file: Boana_sp.4BJAmparoMG3aAAGm671); and (E–F) B. polytaenia (sound file: Boana_polytaeniaNovFriburRJ1bLBM_AAGmt). See Appendix 2 for additional information on sound files." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7818751/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7818745>
    dc:description "FIG. 1. Scatterplot of the two first axes of discriminant analyses of principal components (DAPC) on the (A) morphometric (9 first Principal Components, ca. 95% retained variance) and (B) acoustic (5 first Principal Components, ca. 95% retained variance) datasets of the tree partitions." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7818745/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7818753>
    dc:description "FIG. 5. Oscillograms depicting the variation in the envelope structure of the ‘‘A'' calls of Boana guarinimirim sp. nov. (A) ‘‘A'' call with a decreasing amplitude modulation; a short (B) and a long (C) ‘‘A'' call with irregular amplitude modulations (sound files: Boana_guarinimirimFornoGrandeES2aIV_AAG671; Boana_guarinimirimFornoGrandeES4aPM_AAGm671 and FNJV0040231, respectively)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7818753/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7818755>
    dc:description "FIG. 6. Holotype (CFBH 46043) of Boana guarinimirim sp. nov. in life. (A) Dorsolateral; (B) ventral and (C) dorsolateral view showing the coloration of hidden surfaces of thighs." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7818755/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7818759>
    dc:description "FIG. 8. Distribution of five species within the B. polytaenia clade in southeastern Brazil (Faivovich et al., 2021; Santos et al., 2009), including that of B. guarinimirim sp. nov." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7818759/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7818757>
    dc:description "FIG. 7. Color variation of Boana guarinimirim sp. nov. in life. Dorsolateral view of the paratypes AAG-UFU 6773 (top left), AAG-UFU 6800 (top right), AAG-UFU 6772 (bottom left), and dorsal view of AAG-UFU 6774. Scratch markings produced during aggressive interactions can be noticed on the dorsum of specimens." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7818757/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

